{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, given the sheer size of the model weights, more often than not, it is necessary to quantize the models to lower precision so that their memory footprint is reduced, and the traffic between on-chip and DRAM memory is smaller.",
    "To this end, MELT's converter is able to resolve and download models from git or huggingface and convert their weights to the respective format.",
    "This format varies both in terms of the ML framework, as well as the hardware executing the network.",
    "The supported formats and quantization methods are depicted in Tab. 3.",
    "The original models were downloaded 4 on a given dataset and reporting its accuracy."
  ]
}